// MongoDB Start From Here

Model the following food service industry information as a graph
model, and answer the following queries using Cypher.
Consider food service industries like ZOMATO, Swiggy around us.
Popular restaurants are connected to these industries to increase sell.
A person order food through this industry and get offers. A person give
rate(1-5 stars) to company its facility/facilities. and can recommend this
to his/her friends.

4. Identify the labels and relationships, along with their properties, and
draw a high-level Graph model. 

5. Create nodes and relationships, along with their properties, and
visualize your actual Graph model. 

CREATE
(p1:Person {name:'Sahil', age:25}),
(p2:Person {name:'Sara', age:30}),
(p3:Person {name:'Rahul', age:28}),

(fs1:FoodService {name:'Swiggy'}),
(fs2:FoodService {name:'Zomato'}),

(r1:Restaurant {name:'Tandoori Tales', area:'Indiranagar', rating:5}),
(r2:Restaurant {name:'Pizza Hub', area:'Koramangala', rating:4}),
(r3:Restaurant {name:'Burger King', area:'Indiranagar', rating:3}),

(o1:Order {order_id:1, date:'2023-01-01'}),
(o2:Order {order_id:2, date:'2023-01-01'}),
(o3:Order {order_id:3, date:'2023-02-01'}),

(p1)-[:PLACED]->(o1),
(p2)-[:PLACED]->(o2),
(p3)-[:PLACED]->(o3),

(o1)-[:FROM]->(r1),
(o2)-[:FROM]->(r2),
(o3)-[:FROM]->(r3),

(o1)-[:USING]->(fs1),
(o2)-[:USING]->(fs1),
(o3)-[:USING]->(fs2),

(p1)-[:RECOMMENDED]->(r1),
(p2)-[:RECOMMENDED]->(r2);


6. Answer the Queries.

a. Count no. of customers who place order on â€œ1/1/2023â€
MATCH (p:Person)-[:PLACED]->(o:Order {date:'2023-01-01'})
RETURN count(p) AS TotalCustomers;

b. List the names of customers whose name starts with S and place order using Swiggy  
MATCH (p:Person)-[:PLACED]->(o:Order)-[:USING]->(fs:FoodService {name:'Swiggy'})
WHERE p.name STARTS WITH 'S'
RETURN p.name;

c. List the names of hotels with high rating (>=4).
MATCH (r:Restaurant)
WHERE r.rating >= 4
RETURN r.name, r.rating;

d. List the most recommended hotels in....... area.
MATCH (p:Person)-[:RECOMMENDED]->(r:Restaurant {area:'Indiranagar'})
RETURN r.name, count(p) AS Recommendations
ORDER BY Recommendations DESC
LIMIT 1;
